// // This module performs a modified exclusive OR (XOR) operation on two input signals (A and B), followed by a standard XOR operation with a third input signal (GIN). The modification to the initial XOR operation between A and B is that the result is inverted before being XORed with GIN. This module can be utilized in various digital logic circuits, including but not limited to arithmetic units, parity generators/checkers, and certain types of error detection or correction schemes. Its primary function to generate a sum output (SUM) that is dependent on the logical combination of its inputs, which could be part of a larger arithmetic or logical operation within a digital system.
module XXOR1 ( A, B, GIN, PHI, SUM );
input  A;
input  B;
input  GIN;
input  PHI;
output SUM;
   assign SUM = ( ~ (A ^ B)) ^ GIN;
endmodule
